name: Nebuliser
description: Delivers medication in mist form for inhalation.

name: Inhaler
description: Portable device for administering aerosolized medication.

name: Oxygen Therapy
description: Provides supplemental oxygen to patients.

name: Nasal High Flow
description: Delivers high flow rates of oxygen through nasal cannula.

name: Suctioning
description: Removing secretions from the airway.

name: Continuous Positive Airway Pressure
description: Provides continuous airway pressure to keep airways open.

name: Non-invasive Ventilation
description: Provides variable airway pressure for inhalation and exhalation.

name: Mechanical Ventilation
description: Machine-assisted breathing for patients unable to breathe independently.

name: Tracheostomy
description: Surgical opening in the trachea for breathing support.

name: Chest Physiotherapy
description: Techniques to help clear mucus from the lungs and airways.

name: Endotracheal Intubation
description: Insertion of a tube into the trachea to maintain an open airway.

name: Bag-Valve-Mask
description: Handheld device to provide positive pressure ventilation.

name: Oropharygeal Airway
description: Rigid plastic tube inserted into the mouth to help maintain the airway.

name: Nasopharygeal Airway
description: Flexible tube inserted into the nostril to bypass upper airway obstruction.

name: Endotracheal Tube
description: Tube inserted into the airway to assist breathing and provide oxygen.

name: Intravenous Fluids
description: Administration of fluids directly into a vein.

name: Cannula
description: Small tube inserted into a vein to provide venous access for fluid administration.

name: Central Line
description: Catheter placed into a large vein for long-term access.

name: PICC Line
description: Peripherally Inserted Central Catheter for long-term intravenous access.

name: Port-a-Cath
description: Implanted port under the skin for long-term intravenous access.

name: Hickmann Line
description: Central venous catheter tunneled under the skin for long term access.

name: Midline Catheter
description: Catheter inserted into a peripheral vein for intermediate-term intravenous access.

name: Subcutaneous Infusion
description: Administration of fluids under the skin for absorption.

name: Arterial Line
description: Device used to administer continuous subcutaneous infusions of medication.

name: Syringe Driver
description: Catheter placed into an artery for continuous blood pressure monitoring and blood sampling.

name: Catheter
description: Tube inserted into the bladder to drain urine.

name: Foley Catheter
description: Indwelling catheter with an inflatable balloon to keep it in place.

name: Suprapubic Catheter
description: Catheter inserted through the abdominal wall into the bladder for urine drainage.

name: Urostomy
description: Surgical creation of an opening in the abdomen for urine to be diverted to an external pouch.

name: Nephrostomy
description: Catheter inserted into the kidney for urine drainage.

name: Colostomy
description: Surgical creation of an opening in the colon to divert waste to an external pouch.

name: Ileostomy
description: Surgical creation of an opening in the ileum to divert waste to an external pouch.

name: Nasogastric tube
description: Tube inserted through the nose into the stomach for short-term feeding or medication administration.

name: PEG Tube
description: Tube inserted through the abdominal wall into the stomach for long-term feeding.

name: Total Parenteral Nutrition
description: Intravenous administration of nutrition when gastrointestinal feeding is not possible.

name: Cooling Blankets
description: Blankets that use circulating water or air to reduce body temperature.

name: Warming Blankets
description: Blankets that use circulating water or air to increase body temperature.

name: Heat Packs
description: Packs filled with gel or other materials that provide heat when activated, used to relieve pain and increase temperature.

name: Ice Packs
description: Packs filled with ice or gel that provide cold therapy to reduce swelling and lower body temperature.

name: Defibrillator
description: Device that delivers a dose of electric current to the heart to treat life-threatening cardiac arrhythmias.

name: Pacemaker
description: Device implanted to regulate the heart rate in patients with arrhythmias or heart block.

name: Percutaneous Coronary Intervention
description: Non-surgical procedure that improves blood flow to the heart by using a catheter to place a stent in a coronary artery.

name: Isolation Precautions
description: Practices used to prevent the spread of infectious agents by isolating patients who are infected or colonised.

name: Hand Hygiene
description: Regular and proper hand washing or sanitizing to prevent the spread of infections.

name: Personal Protective Equipment
description: Equipment such as gloves, masks, gowns, and face shields used to protect healthcare workers from infection.

name: Physiotherapy
description: Use of physical methods such as exercise and massage to restore function and reduce pain.

name: Occupational Therapy
description: Therapy focused on helping patients perform daily activities and improve quality of life.
